## Quiz

?? The equation $\text{CH}_4 + 2\,\text{O}_2 \rightarrow \text{CO}_2 + 2\,\text{H}_2\text{O}$ is balanced for atoms. What else must be conserved, and how can we check it here?
>> Charge. Every species in this reaction is neutral, so net charge is zero on both sides — automatically balanced. For ionic reactions we'd need to sum up ionic charges on both sides and verify they match.

?? Why is combustion exothermic — where does the 890 kJ/mol of energy come from?
>> Bond energies. The C-H bonds in methane (~413 kJ/mol each × 4) and the O=O bond in oxygen (~498 kJ/mol × 2) are weaker than the bonds formed: C=O (~799 kJ/mol × 2) and O-H (~463 kJ/mol × 4). Net result: less energy stored in bonds on the product side, released as heat.
